body:
Hogge

Purple T2.5 shoulder, mistakenly sold to NPC. Contacted GM in the game and replied: Ratchet City Garbage Collector retrieved it. Arrived at Ratchet City and had a conversation with NPC, prompting: "You do not have any items that can be restored." Misoperation occurred on the same day, March 7, 2024, between 13:00 and 15:40. Equipped with purple T2.5, although there were a small amount (not exceeding 20) of garbage items sold. Contact the in-game GM again and ask me to provide feedback on the bug. In theory, the equipment will appear on the garbage collector list, and other game players have also reported bugs in the equipment recovery function
Steps for reproducing bugs:

1. Summon repair robots and sell purple items;
2. Have a conversation with the garbage collector in Ratchet City, hoping to retrieve the item;
3. Meets the conditions for retrieving items, but NPC reminds that the item recovery list is empty;

